  <summary>6/29/1988--Introduced.
Amends the Internal Revenue Code to apply to livestock used for draft, breeding, dairy, or sporting purposes a special rule that permits a farmer or rancher who sells livestock solely because of drought conditions to elect to defer until the following year the taxation of the resulting income.</summary>
